# timeline/

## Purpose

The timeline folder stores:
- historical development images,
- milestone artifacts,
- conceptual evolution snapshots,
- and visual records of major discoveries
inside the BIT-X∞ expeditionary process.

---

# Suggested Timeline Structure

```text
timeline/
├── 2026_05_20_operator_01_birth.png
├── 2026_05_20_bit_xinfinity_launch.png
├── future_runtime_discovery_01.png
└── future_operator_artifacts/
```

---

# Timeline Philosophy

The timeline is not intended to function as:
- a strict academic chronology,
- nor a formal proof archive.

Instead, it acts as:
- a living memory trail,
- a symbolic research log,
- and a historical reflection of the evolving BIT-X∞ journey.

---

# Visual Style Recommendation

Recommended visual atmosphere:
- futuristic engineering
- runtime systems aesthetics
- adaptive geometry
- boundary-field structures
- swarm topology
- coherence vs entropy contrast
- dark technological tone
- blockchain-style archival framing

Avoid:
- excessive mystical symbolism
- “ultimate theory” visuals
- overclaim-heavy design language

The visual identity should remain:
- exploratory,
- grounded,
- engineering-oriented,
- and expeditionary in spirit.
